    "abstractNote": "Here I establish the close relationship between a large portion of the Syriac <i>Treatise on the Composition of Man</i> attributed to A\u1e25\u016bdemmeh An\u1e6d\u012bpa\u1e6dr\u014ds, originally published by Chabot in 1943, and the Greek pseudo-Hippocratic treatise originally published as <i>On the Formation of Man</i> by Jouanna in 2006, arguing that one of these texts must be a translation of the other. While firm conclusions about the direction, place and time of this translation must await an improved edition of the Syriac text, I make several suggestions on these points as well. I also show that the Greek pseudo-Hippocratic text may need to be revised, since certain manuscripts consistently agree with the Syriac against others.",
